	<body>
		<h2>Toolbar</h2>
		<p><img src="images/toolbar.png" alt="Toolbar" width="497" height="55" /></p>
		<p>
			The toolbar gives easy access to many of the features and tools within the 3D Data Viewer.
			The items of the toolbar are described below.
		</p>
		<hr/>
		<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">
		  <tr class="odd">
		    <td><img src="images/toolbar_openLayer.png" alt="Open Layer" width="23" height="23" /></td>
		    <td>
		    	<strong>Open layer</strong>
		    	<p>Open a layer definition file from the local filesystem.</p>
		    </td>
		  </tr>
		  <tr>
		    <td><img src="images/toolbar_wms.png" alt="WMS Browser" width="23" height="23" /></td>
		    <td>
		    	<strong>Launch <span class="UIElementReference">WMS Browser</span></strong>
		    	<p>Browse, search and import layers from WMS servers around the world.</p>
		    </td>
		  </tr>
		  <tr class="odd">
		    <td><img src="images/toolbar_saveImage.png" alt="Save Image" width="23" height="23" /></td>
		    <td>
		    	<strong>Save image</strong>
		    	<p>Capture and save a geo-referenced image from the surface of the globe.</p>
		    </td>
		  </tr>
		  <tr>
		    <td><img src="images/toolbar_defaultView.png" alt="Default View" width="23" height="23" /></td>
		    <td>
		    	<strong>Default view</strong>
		    	<p>Return the camera to the default view.</p>
		    </td>
		  </tr>
		  <tr class="odd">
		    <td><img src="images/toolbar_gotoCoordinates.png" alt="Go to coordinates..." width="23" height="23" /></td>
		    <td>
		    	<strong>Go to coordinates</strong>
		    	<p>Zoom to specified coordinates on the globe.</p>
		    </td>
		  </tr>
		  <tr>
		    <td><img src="images/toolbar_fullScreen.png" alt="Full Screen" width="23" height="23" /></td>
		    <td>
		    	<strong>Full screen</strong>
		    	<p>Switch to and from full screen mode</p>
		    </td>
		  </tr>
		  <tr class="odd">
		    <td><img src="images/toolbar_search.png" alt="Search" width="23" height="23" /></td>
		    <td>
		    	<strong>Toggle <span class="UIElementReference">Search</span> panel</strong>
		    	<p>
		    		Show/hide the <span class="UIElementReference">Search</span> panel. 
		    		<br/>
		    		Allows you to locate and zoom to specific places on the globe.
		    	</p>
		    </td>
		  </tr>
		  <tr>
		    <td><img src="images/toolbar_places.png" alt="Places" width="23" height="23" /></td>
		    <td>
		    	<strong>Toggle <span class="UIElementReference">Places</span> panel</strong>
		    	<p>
		    		Show/hide the <span class="UIElementReference">Places</span> panel.
		    		<br/>
		    		Allows you to save and manage places, annotations and animations.
		    	</p>
		    </td>
		  </tr>
		  <tr class="odd">
		    <td><img src="images/toolbar_layers.png" alt="Layers" width="23" height="23" /></td>
		    <td>
		    	<strong>Toggle <span class="UIElementReference">Layers</span> panel</strong>
		    	<p>
		    		Show/hide the <span class="UIElementReference">Layers</span> panel.
		    		<br/>
		    		Allows you to browse and manipulate data layers that are shown on the globe.
		    	</p>
		    </td>
		  </tr>
		  <tr>
		    <td><img src="images/toolbar_datasets.png" alt="Datasets" width="23" height="23" /></td>
		    <td>
		    	<strong>Toggle <span class="UIElementReference">Datasets</span> panel</strong>
		    	<p>
		    		Show/hide the <span class="UIElementReference">Layers</span> panel.
		    		<br/>
		    		Allows you to add additional data layers to the globe.
		    	</p>
		    </td>
		  </tr>
		  <tr class="odd">
		    <td><img src="images/toolbar_verticalExaggeration.png" alt="Vertical exaggeration" width="23" height="23" /></td>
		    <td>
		    	<strong>Toggle <span class="UIElementReference">Vertical exaggeration</span> panel</strong>
		    	<p>
		    		Show/hide the <span class="UIElementReference">Layers</span> panel.
		    		<br/>
		    		Allows you to control the exaggeration applied to vertical distances on the globe.
		    	</p>
		    </td>
		  </tr>
		  <tr>
		    <td><img src="images/toolbar_worldMap.png" alt="World map" width="23" height="23" /></td>
		    <td>
		    	<strong>Toggle <span class="UIElementReference">World Map</span> overlay</strong>
		    	<p>
		    		Provides a visual indication of the geographic extent of the current view.
		    	</p>
		    </td>
		  </tr>
		  <tr class="odd">
		    <td><img src="images/toolbar_compass.png" alt="Compass" width="23" height="23" /></td>
		    <td>
		    	<strong>Toggle <span class="UIElementReference">Compass</span> overlay</strong>
		    	<p>
		    		Provides a visual indication of the orientation of the current view.
		    	</p>
		    </td>
		  </tr>
		  <tr>
		    <td><img src="images/toolbar_scalebar.png" alt="Scale bar" width="23" height="23" /></td>
		    <td>
		    	<strong>Toggle <span class="UIElementReference">Scale bar</span> overlay</strong>
		    	<p>
		    		Provides a visual indication of the distance scale of the current view.
		    	</p>
		    </td>
		  </tr>
		  <tr class="odd">
		    <td><img src="images/toolbar_navigationControls.png" alt="Navigation controls" width="23" height="23" /></td>
		    <td>
		    	<strong>Toggle <span class="UIElementReference">Navigation</span> overlay</strong>
		    	<p>
		    		Provides access to the on-screen navigation controls (see <a href="Navigation.jsp">Navigation Controls</a>).
		    	</p>
		    </td>
		  </tr>
		  <tr>
		    <td><img src="images/toolbar_graticule.png" alt="Graticule" width="23" height="23" /></td>
		    <td>
		    	<strong>Toggle <span class="UIElementReference">Graticule</span> overlay</strong>
		    	<p>
		    		Displays a graticule (latitude/longitude) lines overlayed on the globe.
		    	</p>
		    </td>
		  </tr>
		  <tr class="odd">
		    <td><img src="images/toolbar_crosshair.png" alt="Crosshair" width="23" height="23" /></td>
		    <td>
		    	<strong>Toggle <span class="UIElementReference">Crosshair</span> overlay</strong>
		    	<p>
		    		Displays a crosshair at the centre of the current view.
		    	</p>
		    </td>
		  </tr>
		  <tr>
		    <td><img src="images/toolbar_preferences.png" alt="Preferences..." width="23" height="23" /></td>
		    <td>
		    	<strong>Launch the <span class="UIElementReference">Preferences</span> dialog</strong>
		    	<p>
		    		Allows application settings to be configured.
		    	</p>
		    </td>
		  </tr>
		</table>
		<hr/>
		<p>&nbsp;</p>
	</body>
</html>
